===Player representation by league system===
League systems with twenty or more players represented are listed. England included two [[Premier League]] clubs based in Wales, [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]] and [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]] (five World Cup squad members played for these clubs); the United States included three [[Major League Soccer|MLS]] clubs based in Canada, [[Toronto FC]], [[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]] and [[CF Montréal|Montreal Impact]] (three World Cup squad members played for these clubs); and France included one [[Ligue 1]] club based in Monaco, [[AS Monaco FC|AS Monaco]] (four World Cup squad members played for this club). In all, World Cup squad members played for clubs in 54 countries, and played in 51 different national leagues.<ref name="guardian"/>

